ks.framework.interfaces
Interface IProcessMessage

All Known Implementing Classes:
Client, FrontEnd, Processor
public interface IProcessMessage

Interface to declare the processing of a message.

The message may be a command, request or adminCommand. Sometimes the class implementing this interface processes the command to generate a request. Other times, the class implementing the interface is passing along the command (without processing) along to another class who is responsible for the actual processing.

Author:
George Heineman
